<section xml:id="sec-4-2-Solving_Triangles_Using_the_Law_of_Cosines" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
    <title>Solving Triangles Using the Law of Cosines</title>
    <p><em>Solving Triangles Using the Law of Cosines</em> solves triangles in the Side-Angle-Side (SAS) and 
        Side-Side-Side (SSS) cases. It refers to the Law of Sines to complete the solving process, so 
        familiarity with <xref ref="sec-4-1-Solving_Triangles_Using_the_Law_of_Sines_Part_I" text="title"/> is helpful, 
        but not necessary. Each problem could be solved using only the Law of Cosines. The remaining case, the 
        ambiguous Side-Side-Angle (SSA) case is shown in 
        <xref ref="sec-4-3-Solving_Triangles_Using_the_Law_of_Sines_Part_II" text="title"/>.  
        The proof of the Law of Cosines is not given here, only examples where the Law of Cosines 
        is used to solve triangles</p>
        
